      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 1297.3823977070215,
      "y": 51.4732596564063,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 651.0795654654503,
      "height": 100,
      "seed": 2094405699,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755262432224,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Inheritance/Generalisation: (is-a)\nwhere one class (subclass) inherits the attributes and methods of\nanother class(superclass)\nEx: Dog is a Animal",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Inheritance/Generalisation: (is-a)\nwhere one class (subclass) inherits the attributes and methods of\nanother class(superclass)\nEx: Dog is a Animal",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 573,
      "versionNonce": 49866403,
      "index": "aK",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "jUELD9iOeVwG5-Y-QXy8P",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 1296.4680344657336,
      "y": 184.40851896553067,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 655.9195556640625,
      "height": 75,
      "seed": 59774947,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755262432224,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Realisation/Implementation: \nwhere one ore more classes implements the method of an interface \nEx: EmailNotification implements Notification",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Realisation/Implementation: \nwhere one ore more classes implements the method of an interface \nEx: EmailNotification implements Notification",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 514,
      "versionNonce": 1919453453,
      "index": "aL",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "i1y5PrvGE9GGDlWvX2xnO",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 1298.4704810224057,
      "y": 294.09389773154544,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 637.7794189453125,
      "height": 75,
      "seed": 237577091,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755262432224,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Dependency: (uses)\nwhere change in one class(supplier) may affect change in another \nclass(client)",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Dependency: (uses)\nwhere change in one class(supplier) may affect change in another \nclass(client)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 821,
      "versionNonce": 755636803,
      "index": "aM",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "rfPViy8y5phg9-pun6X37",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 2216.917987959777,
      "y": -336.04764032489766,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 636.5595092773438,
      "height": 150,
      "seed": 1692384035,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755262432224,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Single Responsibility Principle (SRP): \nA class should have only 1 reason to change, that means \nit should have single responsibility\n\nViolation: One class where it does auth, register, notification, log\nFix: Multiple classes to do only 1 thing",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Single Responsibility Principle (SRP): \nA class should have only 1 reason to change, that means \nit should have single responsibility\n\nViolation: One class where it does auth, register, notification, log\nFix: Multiple classes to do only 1 thing",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 1129,
      "versionNonce": 536559571,
      "index": "aN",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "FeElGmH_hyLriZRtHeSm_",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 2214.3543572397366,
      "y": -132.15675489918794,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 672.1795654296875,
      "height": 175,
      "seed": 1143103171,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1760054853272,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Op   en for Extension, Closed for Modification (OCP):\naims to extend the functionality of the class without changing the \nexisting behaviour of the class to avoid unknown bugs\n\nViolation: Create one class with multiple strategies method within it\nFix: Use interface and let other strategies classes  implement it, as \nrequired add more strategies without affecting the existing ones",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Op   en for Extension, Closed for Modification (OCP):\naims to extend the functionality of the class without changing the \nexisting behaviour of the class to avoid unknown bugs\n\nViolation: Create one class with multiple strategies method within it\nFix: Use interface and let other strategies classes  implement it, as \nrequired add more strategies without affecting the existing ones",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 788,
      "versionNonce": 1374935523,
      "index": "aO",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "iXSS7TY4s80lB935OLk0_",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 2211.2727990499743,
      "y": 107.4878346234982,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 718.199462890625,
      "height": 175,
      "seed": 1452248675,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755262432224,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Liskov Substitution Principle (LSP):\nobjects of parent class should be replaceable by objects of child class,\nwhich ensures that child class didn't break anything wrt to its parent \n\nViolation: Overriding method in child class with weird or unexpected error \nFix: Don't do the above\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Liskov Substitution Principle (LSP):\nobjects of parent class should be replaceable by objects of child class,\nwhich ensures that child class didn't break anything wrt to its parent \n\nViolation: Overriding method in child class with weird or unexpected error \nFix: Don't do the above\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 672,
      "versionNonce": 1338173319,
      "index": "aP",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "bRfc46_6r-fivrBoF61gK",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 2211.9135660573347,
      "y": 331.7563060689863,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 720.9993896484375,
      "height": 150,
      "seed": 1861601795,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1758744454040,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Interface Segregation Principle (ISP):\nDesign interfaces such that no clients are forced to implement interfaces\nthey don't use \n\nViolation: Creating one interface for everything \nFix: Proper grouping/segregation of interfaces based on the need. ",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Interface Segregation Principle (ISP):\nDesign interfaces such that no clients are forced to implement interfaces\nthey don't use \n\nViolation: Creating one interface for everything \nFix: Proper grouping/segregation of interfaces based on the need. ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 752,
      "versionNonce": 516203907,
      "index": "aQ",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "73-sRuxKdm8Fc6OWljan2",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 2210.977366917371,
      "y": 544.6991611071498,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "width": 744.6396020650864,
      "height": 150,
      "seed": 39031203,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755262432224,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP):\nHigh level modules shouldn't depend on low level modules, both should depend\non abstractions\n\nViolation: Use single client like Gmail Client in a service like EmailService \nFix: Create interface for client and then use it in EmailService",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Dependency Inversion Principle (DIP):\nHigh level modules shouldn't depend on low level modules, both should depend\non abstractions\n\nViolation: Use single client like Gmail Client in a service like EmailService \nFix: Create interface for client and then use it in EmailService",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
