      "fontSize": 17.3647437124314,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "\nWhen we have multiple ways/strategy to do the\nsame thing, so based on the request we want to use\nthe correct behaviour \n\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\nWhen we have multiple ways/strategy to do the\nsame thing, so based on the request we want to use\nthe correct behaviour \n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "version": 1015,
      "versionNonce": 1481874253,
      "index": "aX",
      "isDeleted": false,
      "id": "XJJLzIApqzGMnUgnooahP",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "x": 4083.764230030718,
      "y": -116.33693397429306,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "width": 598.8314819335938,
      "height": 160,
      "seed": 400119555,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1755262432224,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "text": "\nGenerally, We could create many instances of a class  but for some cases, \nWe only need 1 instance so that every service using this instance talks \nto the same one. \n\nThis is where SingleTon comes into picture and we restrict the instantiation\nof the class\n",
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\nGenerally, We could create many instances of a class  but for some cases, \nWe only need 1 instance so that every service using this instance talks \nto the same one. \n\nThis is where SingleTon comes into picture and we restrict the instantiation\nof the class\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
